r-reward-better\/","url_meta":{"origin":21803,"position":0},"title":"Umar II on Sabr: Reward of patience better than material blessings","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 7, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Muhammad ibn Amr reported: Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, said upon the pulpit, \u201cAllah does not grant a servant a blessing and then removes the blessing, then compensates him with patience in place of what was removed, but that what he was granted is better\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3389,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/06\/16\/work-rizq-like-birds\/","url_meta":{"origin":21803,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Reliance: Must work for provision like the birds","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 16, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf you were to rely upon Allah with reliance due to Him, He would provide for you just as He provides for the birds. They go out in the morning with empty stomachs and return\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33873,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/01\/06\/divorce-triple-talaq\/","url_meta":{"origin":21803,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Divorce: Triple talaq in the time of the Prophet, Abu Bakr, and Umar","author":"Abu Amina Elias","da